SIMPLE: loosestrife
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loosestrife
<hw>Loose"strife`</hw> <pr>(l⟦oomac⟧s"str⟦imac⟧f`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The name of several species of
plants of the genus <gen>Lysimachia</gen>, having small star-shaped
flowers, usually of a yellow color.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any species
of the genus <gen>Lythrum</gen>, having purple, or, in some species,
crimson flowers.</def> <au>Gray.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 869 --></p>

<p><cs><col><b>False loosestrife</b></col>, <cd>a plant of the genus
<gen>Ludwigia</gen>, which includes several species, most of which are
found in the United States.</cd> -- <col><b>Tufted
loosestrife</b></col>, <cd>the plant <spn>Lysimachia thyrsiflora</spn>,
found in the northern parts of the United States and in Europe.</cd>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loosish</ent>⟦br⟧
